1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION honoring Cindy Hoye for her
2 longstanding service to the Indiana State Fair Commission.
3 Whereas, Cindy Hoye has dedicated nearly 40 years to the
4 Indiana State Fair Commission;
5 Whereas, Cindy Hoye became the executive director in 2004,
6 having previously served for 16 years as the commission's
7 marketing director;
8 Whereas, Under her leadership, the commission oversaw
9 significant projects, including the renovation of the Corteva
10 Coliseum and the construction of the Indiana Farm Bureau
11 Fall Creek Pavilion. She also played a key role in expanding
12 4-H programming;
13 Whereas, In addition, Cindy Hoye helped attract prestigious
20262346
HR 1516/DI 140 2026

2
1 national track and field events to Indianapolis and the
2 fairgrounds, such as the NCAA Division II Indoor Track and
3 Field Championships, the Big Ten Conference Indoor Track
4 and Field Championships, the Hoosier State Relays, and other
5 major meets; and
6 Whereas, Cindy Hoye plans to retire from her position as
7 executive director in March of this year: Therefore,
8 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
9 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
10 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
11 honors Cindy Hoye for her longstanding service to the Indiana
12 State Fair Commission.
13 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
14 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to State
15 Representative Beau Baird for distribution.
